news_raw.title: Nasdaq Is on Track for Best Start to September Since 2010
news_raw.summary: The Nasdaq Composite is up 3.9% so far this month, which would be its best start to September since it rose 8.9% in the first 10 trading days of September 2010, according to Dow Jones Market Data.  September is typically a tough time for stocks: The Nasdaq Composite has averaged a decline of 0.9% during the month going back to 1971, according to Dow Jones Market Data, while the S&P has averaged a 1.1% decline going back to 1928.

news_raw.summary: All eyes are on the Federal Reserve a week ahead of the US central bank's September FOMC meeting, which is likely to result in a cut to interest rates. Manulife Investment Management head of developed-market fixed income Jeff Given joins Josh Lipton for a conversation about the Fed's current strategy to control inflation after August's disappointing jobs numbers.
